claim.claim-text:
An endoscope apparatus comprising:
a light source portion including light sources that irradiate living tissue with an excitation light for generating fluorescence and a reference light for generating a reflected light alternately;
an image pickup portion including image pickup devices having a predetermined number of pixels for picking up images of the fluorescence generated by the irradiation of the living tissue with the excitation light and a reflected light of the reference light reflected by the living tissue;
a signal processing portion that generates image signals from signals picked up by the image pickup portion;
an addition processing portion that generates, from signals of the image pickup portion obtained when the image of the fluorescence is picked up or the image signals of the fluorescence generated by the signal processing portion, addition processed signals of fluorescence in which a plurality of adjacent pixels are added;
a light quantity control portion that controls a quantity of at least one of the excitation light and the reference light so as to maintain a predetermined light quantity ratio between quantities of the excitation light and the reference light from the addition processed signals of the fluorescence generated by the addition processing portion and reflected light signals as the image signals of the reflected light generated by the signal processing portion on the basis of change in a number of pixels to be added by the addition processing portion; and
a superimposition processing portion that performs a processing of superimposing the addition processed signals of the fluorescence and the reflected light signals on each other and outputs, to a display portion, superimposed image signals in which the addition processed signals and the reflected light signals are superimposed, with the predetermined light quantity ratio being maintained.

A method for controlling light quantity of fluorescence imaging, the method comprising:
an irradiating step in which a light source portion irradiates living tissue with an excitation light for generating fluorescence and a reference light for generating a reflected light alternately;
an image pickup step in which an image pickup portion including image pickup devices having a predetermined number of pixels picks up images of the fluorescence generated by the irradiation of the living tissue with the excitation light and a reflected light of the reference light reflected by the living tissue;
a signal processing step in which a signal processing portion generates image signals from signals picked up in the image pickup step;
an addition processing step in which an addition processing portion generates addition processed signals of fluorescence obtained by addition processing among a plurality of adjacent pixels from the signals obtained by picking up the fluorescence in the image pickup step or from the image signals of the fluorescence generated in the signal processing step;
a light quantity control step in which a light quantity control portion controls a quantity of at least one of the excitation light and the reference light so as to maintain a predetermined light quantity ratio between quantities of the excitation light and the reference light from the addition processed signals of the fluorescence generated in the addition processing step and reflected light signals as the image signals of the reflected light generated in the signal processing step on the basis of change in the number of pixels to be added in the addition processing step; and
a superimposition signal generating step in which a superimposition processing portion performs a processing of superimposing the addition processed signals of the fluorescence and the reflected light signals on each other and outputs, to a display portion, superimposed image signals in which the addition processed signals and the reflected light signals are superimposed, with the predetermined light quantity ratio being maintained,
wherein, when the number of pixels to be subjected to the addition processing is changed, the light quantity control step controls the light quantity of the excitation light on the basis of information on the number of pixels immediately after the change of the number of pixels.
